President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Christopher Hart is nominated for Chairman of the National Transportation Safety Board, John W. Leslie, Jr. is nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the African Development Foundation, Donald L. Pereira is appointed as Commissioner of the United States Section of the Great Lakes Fishery Commission, and Douglas L. Stang is also appointed as Commissioner of the United States Section of the Great Lakes Fishery Commission. These individuals bring a wealth of experience and dedication to their new roles.